/*
  hello.du -- a maximum effort "hello world"

  This prints a verbose but nice hello using the flexible
  multi-line strings and markdown -> ansi from our stdlib.

  For added fun we check the system environment to see if
  the user has $NOCOLOR set so we skip making pretty ANSI.
*/

md = require("markdown")

// make a friendly multi-line markdon welcome message
welcome = """
  # Hello Brave Explorer

  **Welcome!** I am humbled by your willingness to give this new thing a try. I've worked very hard to make `duso` a simple and powerful language that's easy for humans and LLMs to use and understand.

  I hope this is the start of something great for you.

  **Happy scripting!**

  > â€” Dave Balmer
"""

// respect user's color preferences
nocolor = env("NOCOLOR")
if nocolor then
  // keep it simple
  print(welcome)
else
  // format the markdown and make it colorful
  pretty = md.ansi(welcome)

  // print it out
  print(pretty)
end
